The subfamily Dilobinae is Holarctic in distribution and comprises 13 described species. Six species occur in North America, one in AB. There have been no recent revisions of the subfamily, but the AB species (
Raphia frater
) was treated by Forbes (1954) , Covell (1984) , and Handfield (1999) . Th e larva was illustrated in Wagner et al. (1997) .
